               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Gadla Za-Mikāʾel ʾAragāwi "Vita of Za-Mikāʾel ʾAragāwi" (fols.
                     5ra-35rb l.9)
 II) Taʾammǝra Za-Mikāʾel ʾAragāwi "Miracles of Za-Mikāʾel
                     ʾAragāwi" (fols. 35rb l.10-46vb)
 - Introductory homily (fols. 35rb
                     l.10-36vb l.13)
 - 5 miracles (fols. 36vb l.14-46vb)
 III) Malkǝʾa
                     Za-Mikāʾel ʾAragāwi "Image of Za-Mikāʾel ʾAragāwi" (fols. 47ra-50rb)
 IV)
                     Gadla Gabra Krǝstos "Vita of Gabra Krǝstos [St Alexius]" (fols. 50ra-75vb)
                     
 Additio 1.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>The explicit of Text I as presented in I. GUIDI, Il "Gadla ʼAragâwi",
                        Roma 1895 (pp. 35-36 starting with the words: ተፈጸመ፡ ገድሉ፡ ወተኣምሪሁ፡ ለብእሴ፡
                        እግዚአብሔር፡ ቅዱስ፡ ወብፁዕ፡ አቡነ፡ አረጋዊ...) is missing.</note>
                     <note>For the collection of miracles of Za-Mikāʾel ʾAragāwi see A. BRITA, I
                        Racconti Tradizionali sulla "Seconda Cristianizzazione" dell'Etiopia, il
                        Ciclo Agriografico dei Nove Santi, Napoli 2010, pp. 232-34.</note>
                     <note>Text IV comprises the "List of Saints" (<locus target="#63ra">63ra</locus> l.2-64vb l.20), the "Song of Dāwit" (<locus target="#64vb">64vb</locus> l.20-69va l.7) and the longer version of the kidan-scene
                           (<locus target="#66ra">66ra</locus> l.22-69ra l.4).</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
