                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Poor and irregular</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        Scribe: ʿAynä Kʷǝllu Gabra
                        Śǝllāse. According to Additio 1, ʾalaqā ʿAynä Kʷǝllu Gabra Śǝllāse
                        (of Qäqäma?) sold the Ms. Probably he is also the scribe.<date>Beginning of
                           the 20th century</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ለ፡ ዓ፡</abbr> for <expan>ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ </expan> (e.g., <locus target="#5vb">5vb</locus>, 12ra, 21vb, 34rb, 40rab, 50rb,
                              61va)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ለ፡ ዓ፡ ዓ፡</abbr> for <expan>ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ </expan> (e.g., <locus target="#19vb">19vb</locus>, 27vb, 30va, 31rb, 38rb, 46ra,
                              54vb)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ለዓ፡ ዓለ፡</abbr> for <expan>ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ </expan> (e.g., <locus target="#35rb">35rb</locus>)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ለመ፡ ዓለ፡ ዓለ፡</abbr> for <expan>ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ </expan> (e.g., <locus target="#24vb">24vb</locus>)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ሰላ፡</abbr> for <expan>ሰላም፡ </expan> (<locus from="47rb" to="50rb">47rb-50rb</locus>)</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra, names of the protagonists, a few other
                           names (e.g., Madḫāne ʿĀlam, Dabra Dāmmo); a few lines on the incipit page
                           of all texts, incipit of (sub)sections of Texts I, II and IV; Hebrew
                           letters in Text IV (fol. 69va), world salām "salutation" and its
                           abbreviations in Text III; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of
                           Ethiopic numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">The handwriting is characterized by
                        very peculiar shapes of some letters, e.g., ላ and ካ have the left leg highly
                        raised, the right one set on the ruling
                        line.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
